Takes note with appreciation of the reports of the Special Rapporteur on the promotion of truth, justice, reparation and guarantees of non‑recurrence submitted to the Human Rights Council at its forty-eighth, fifty-first and fifty-fourth sessions,
A/HRC/48/60, A/HRC/51/34 and A/HRC/54/24. as well as those submitted to the General Assembly at its seventy-fifth, seventy-sixth and seventy-seventh sessions,
See A/75/174, A/76/180 and A/77/162. and calls upon States to take into due consideration the recommendations contained therein when designing and implementing strategies, policies and measures to address gross human rights violations and serious violations of international humanitarian law within their national context;
